§ AXIOMS  ‼ inherit PRIME_DIRECTIVE
  t∞: F1..F6 = canonical-set  (no-amend-without-spec-bump)
       ≡ adding F7+ = major-version-event
  t∞: features compose-orthogonally
       ≡ ∀ pair (Fi, Fj) : i ≠ j ⇒ no-mutual-blocking
  t∞: no-feature-can-bypass-PRIME-DIRECTIVE
       ≡ F1 AD ¬ leaks Sensitive<biometric>
       ≡ F4 staging ¬ specializes-around F5 IFC-checks
       ≡ F6 observability ¬ exfiltrates raw-paths

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ F1 : AUTODIFF  (Jet<T,N> + GPU-AD-tape + Call-op + scf.* tape + DiffPG)

  § THESIS
    F1 ≡ first-class differentiable computation throughout CSSLv3.
    NOT macro-AD ; NOT ad-hoc-per-call gradient-tape ; instead :
    Jet<T,N> as a number-system + MIR-level AD-tape + structured-
    control-flow tape-recording + DiffPG (differentiable-program-graph).

  § F1.1 — Jet<T,N> higher-order forward-mode AD (T11-D133)
    crate         : cssl-autodiff::jet
    spec-anchor   : specs/17_JETS.csl § TYPE-DEFINITION + § ARITHMETIC-RULES
    type          : Jet<T,N> stores N consecutive Taylor-terms
                    terms[0]   = primal f(x)
                    terms[1]   = 1st deriv f'(x)
                    terms[k]   = kth deriv f^(k)(x)
    operations    : +, -, *, /, sin, cos, exp, log, sqrt, pow
                    higher-order : compose (Faà di Bruno)
                    extras       : hessian_vector_product
    storage       : Jet<T,N> = N-term storage = (N-1)-th order jet
                    (off-by-one trick — stable-Rust without
                     feature(generic_const_exprs))
    consumers     : KAN-runtime sin/cos/pow for spline 2nd-derivs
                    Hyperspectral-KAN-BRDF compose for spectral-basis
                    Inverse-rendering Hessian-vector for 2nd-order optimizer
                    Gaze-saccade prediction (cssl-gaze-collapse)

  § F1.2 — GPU-AD tape + SPIR-V differentiable-shader (T11-D139)
    crate         : cssl-autodiff::gpu
    spec-anchor   : specs/05_AUTODIFF.csl § GPU-AD § SPIR-V-EMISSION
    capability    : MIR-level cssl.ad.* ops emit SPIR-V Capability=Shader
                    + OpExtInst GLSL.std.450 for differentiable-builtins
    forward-mode  : per-thread Jet<f32,N> packed-in-registers for N≤4 ;
                    larger-N spills to shared-memory / SSBO
    backward-mode : tape recorded-in-SSBO ; replay-pass emits backward-grad
                    ¬ checkpointing-yet (DEFERRED to memory-pressure)
    DiffPG        : differentiable-program-graph encoded as MIR-region

  § F1.3 — Call-op auto-dispatch (DiffPG) + scf.* tape-record (T11-D140)
    crate         : cssl-autodiff::call_dispatch
    spec-anchor   : specs/05_AUTODIFF.csl § CALL-OP + § SCF-TAPE
    call-op       : cssl.call routed-through DiffPG-resolver :
                      callee differentiable ⇒ generate dual-call
                      callee non-differentiable ⇒ break-into-tape-checkpoint
    scf.if-tape   : both branches recorded ; replay-walks both for backward
    scf.for-tape  : loop-tape records iter-count + per-iter checkpoint
    scf.while-tape: break-condition recorded ; backward-walk respects
    invariant     : tape-record produces deterministic-replay-bytes
                    same-fwd-trace ⇒ same-bwd-grad bit-equal

  § F1.4 — Substitute (forward-mode pass) + walker + transform
    crate         : cssl-autodiff::{substitute, walker, transform}
    pass          : per-fn forward-mode AD pass
                    consumes : MIR-fn with cssl.ad.* annotations
                    produces : derivative-fn (Jet-typed return)
    walker        : MIR-walker over scf.* + arith-ops emitting tape-record
    rules         : cssl-autodiff::rules — chain-rule per-op-kind

  § PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (F1)
    differentiating Sensitive<biometric|gaze|face|body> values
    ⇒ derivative-fn inherits the Sensitive<...> labels
    ⇒ TelemetryEgress::for_domain(...) STILL refuses to authorize egress
    ⇒ F1 cannot-be-used to launder biometric-data through gradient-step

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ F2 : REFINEMENT-TYPES  (@layout(std430,soa) + struct-alignment validation)

  § THESIS
    F2 ≡ refinement-types over base-types — enables "this struct
    is exactly 72B std430-aligned" to be a TYPE-LEVEL claim that
    the compiler discharges via a refinement-bag.

  § F2.1 — @layout(...) attribute parser (T11-D126)
    crate         : cssl-parse + cssl-hir + cssl-mir::layout_check
    spec-anchor   : specs/03_TYPES.csl § F2 REFINEMENT-TYPES
    syntax        : `@layout(kind, ...) struct FieldCell { ... }`
                    kind ∈ { std140, std430, soa, aos, hot, cold }
    parser-pass   : extracts layout-kinds-with-unknown HirAttr
    validator     : computes natural byte-size + alignment under declared kind
                    emits LAY*-diagnostics on mismatch

  § F2.2 — Stable diagnostic-codes (FROZEN)
    LAY0001 : declared-size ≠ computed-size (e.g. FieldCell ≠ 72B)
    LAY0002 : alignment-violation (per-kind rule)
    LAY0003 : unsupported-combination (e.g. @layout(soa, aos))

  § F2.3 — Refinement-obligation queue → SMT (Phase-2 work)
    bag           : RefinementObligation collected per-validated-struct
    ingestion     : downstream cssl-smt {Verify<Z3>} discharges
    invariant     : F2-refinement consistent with F4 staged-spec
                    (specialized-fn shapes match-refinement post-bake)

  § F2.4 — FieldCell concrete-test (load-bearing)
    `@layout(std430,soa) struct FieldCell { ... }`
    ⇒ size_of(FieldCell) == 72  ‼  enforced
    ⇒ align_of(FieldCell) == 8   ‼  enforced
    ⇒ 9 contiguous u64-rows pack-tight (no-silent-padding)
    runtime-test confirms layout matches §§ 30_v2 § BYTE-LAYOUT

  § PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (F2)
    refinement-types make-explicit the @sensitive labels on struct-fields ;
    cannot silently-elide IFC-information via implicit-conversion
    refinement-discharge audit-logged via cssl-smt {Verify<Z3>} chain

