§ F3 : EFFECT-SYSTEM  (Travel + Crystallize + Sovereign + Conservation rows)

  § THESIS
    F3 ≡ effect-rows are first-class type-system citizens.
    composition-rules are STRUCTURAL ; forbidden-pairs are
    compile-errors ; no runtime override exists.

  § F3.1 — Substrate-effect-rows (T11-D127)
    crate         : cssl-effects::substrate
    spec-anchor   : specs/30_SUBSTRATE.csl § EFFECT-ROWS +
                    Omniverse/02_CSSL/02_EFFECTS.csl § III
    canonical-six : Render Sim Audio Net Save Telemetry  (legacy v1)
    additions S11 : Travel Crystallize Sovereign<S>      (Axiom-2 substrate-relativity)
    composition   : try_compose(rowA, rowB) → Ok(rowAB) | ConflictReason
    diag-codes    : EFR0001..EFR0010 (six base) + EFR0011..EFR0018 (substrate-translation)

  § F3.2 — Conservation + Cosmology rows (T11-D128)
    crate         : cssl-effects::conservation
    rows          : Conservation<{energy|momentum|charge|...}>
                    Cosmology<{rg-flow|substrate-evolution|big-bounce}>
    discipline    : every Phase-6 ENTROPY-BOOK op carries a Conservation<...> row
                    violations panic + audit-entry per spec
    consumers     : cssl-substrate-omega-field Phase-6 hook
                    cssl-wave-solver ψ-norm-conservation
                    cssl-physics-wave momentum-conservation

  § F3.3 — Travel + Crystallize + Sovereign<S> (T11-D127)
    Travel        : substrate-translation effect — moves subject
                    to-different-substrate-region. requires Translate consent-bit.
    Crystallize   : material-recrystallization — re-arranges S facet.
                    requires Recrystallize consent-bit.
    Sovereign<S>  : "this op acts-as Sovereign-S" — checked against cell's
                    sovereignty_handle on every-touch.
    forbidden     : Travel ⊎ Sensitive<surveillance> = compile-error
                    Crystallize ⊎ Sensitive<weapon> = compile-error
                    Sovereign<X> ⊎ Sovereign<Y> X≠Y = compile-error

  § F3.4 — Discipline + Registry + Banned + Substrate
    crate         : cssl-effects::{discipline, registry, banned, substrate}
    discipline    : ordered-insertion + iteration ; no-allocation row-rep
    registry      : table of canonical effect-rows + diag-codes
    banned        : SensitiveDomain enum mirrors specs/11_IFC

  § PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (F3)
    Forbidden-pairs are structural — no caps_grant, no "unsafe-flag", no
    runtime-override. The composition table IS the prime-directive
    encoding at the effect-system layer.

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ F4 : STAGED-COMPUTATION  (Comptime-eval + Specialization pass)

  § THESIS
    F4 ≡ @staged fns evaluate-at-compile-time ; per-call-site specialization
    eliminates runtime branching ; #run blocks execute @ comptime.

  § F4.1 — @staged + #run + Specializer (existing scaffold)
    crate         : cssl-staging
    spec-anchor   : specs/06_STAGING.csl + specs/19_FUTAMURA3.csl
    @staged-fn    : argument classification — comptime-known vs runtime
    #run-block    : marks site for comptime-eval
    Specializer   : per-call-site clone + pre-bind + const-prop + DCE +
                    mangled-name emit
    ‼ now active : SpecializerPass migrated to MIR-pass (T11-D142)

  § F4.2 — Comptime-eval evaluator (T11-D141)
    crate         : cssl-staging::comptime
    pipeline      : HIR → synthetic-HirFn → MIR → JIT (cssl-cgen-cpu-cranelift)
                    → invoke → capture-result → encode-bytes → ComptimeResult
    types         : ComptimeValue (Int/Float/Bool/Str/Sym/Unit/Tuple)
                    ComptimeResult (structured + flat-bytes + codecs)
    pre-flight    : effect_scan refuses non-pure #run bodies
                    sandbox::check_sandbox_policy combined effect+result-type guard

  § F4.3 — Bake module (T11-D141)
    crate         : cssl-staging::bake
    bake_result   : embed ComptimeResult into MIR as arith.constant
    bake_lut      : LUT-bake into cssl.array.assemble
    bake_kan      : KAN-weight bake into cssl.struct.assemble
    consumers     : cssl-substrate-kan KanMaterial weights pre-baked
                    Stage-6 spectral-BRDF tables LUT-baked per-config
                    Wave-Unity stability-Kan weights baked

  § F4.4 — Specialization MIR-pass (T11-D142)
    crate         : cssl-staging::specialize_pass
    pass          : SpecializerPass runs AFTER monomorph + BEFORE AD/IFC/SMT
    pipeline-pos  : per specs/06_STAGING § STAGED-SEMANTICS
    mangling      : per-specialization mangled-name keeps replay-deterministic
    cache         : DEFERRED — keyed by (fn-name, arg-hash, source-hash)
    emit          : specialized-fn with const-folded body

  § F4.5 — Demos (KAN-weight + LUT)
    kan_demo      : KAN-weight comptime-bake demo (D141)
    kan_specialize_demo : end-to-end specialization proving milestone
    lut_demo      : LUT-bake into MIR demo
    mock_evaluator: T11-D141 test-double evaluator

  § PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (F4)
    @staged specialization preserves IFC-labels on baked-values ;
    Sensitive<biometric>-Jet baked into KAN-weights would still
    refuse-egress. comptime-eval forbidden-effect-token list excludes
    {Privilege<Kernel>, Net, Save} unless explicit pre-flight.

