§ F5 : INFORMATION-FLOW-CONTROL  (OnDeviceOnly + Sensitive<biometric|gaze|face|body> + Σ-pass)

  § THESIS
    F5 ≡ values carry IFC-labels ; egress-checks happen at-type-level ;
    no value crosses a confidentiality-boundary without a declass-policy.

  § F5.1 — Sensitive<dom> domain enum (T11-D129)
    crate         : cssl-ifc::domain
    spec-anchor   : specs/11_IFC.csl § PRIME-DIRECTIVE ENCODING
    domains       : Privacy Weapon Surveillance Coercion Manipulation
                    Biometric Gaze Face Body  ★ T11-D132
    biometric-family : { Biometric, Gaze, Face, Body } absolute-egress-banned

  § F5.2 — TelemetryEgress capability (T11-D129)
    crate         : cssl-ifc::egress
    type          : TelemetryEgress (zero-sized capability-token)
    constructor   : TelemetryEgress::for_domain(d) refuses biometric-family
                    + Surveillance + Coercion at-COMPILE-TIME ; no unsafe alt
    privilege     : Privilege<*> CANNOT override structural ban
                    (User/System/Kernel/Root/AnthropicAudit/ApockyRoot all-fail)
    P18 BiometricEgress : process-abort if biometric-family value reaches
                          telemetry-ring-boundary at runtime

  § F5.3 — OnDeviceOnly attribute (T11-D129)
    crate         : cssl-ifc::label
    spec-anchor   : specs/11_IFC.csl § ON-DEVICE-ONLY
    intent        : @on-device-only fn cannot be called by code that emits
                    network/file effects in same effect-row
    consumers     : cssl-host-openxr (gaze-tracker fns @on-device-only)
                    cssl-physics-wave (body-tracker fns @on-device-only)

  § F5.4 — EnforcesΣAtCellTouches MIR-pass (T11-D138)
    crate         : cssl-mir::sigma_enforce
    spec-anchor   : Omniverse/02_CSSL/00_LANGUAGE_CONTRACT § VI.D
                    + specs/30_SUBSTRATE_v2 § ENFORCESΣATCELLTOUCHES-PASS
    coverage      : OP_FIELDCELL_{READ|WRITE|MODIFY|DESTROY}
                    + Travel-row + Crystallize-row composing-substrate-translation
    diag-codes    : SIG0001..SIG0010 (stable, frozen)
    discipline    : MUTATION-FREE pass — surfaces-violations ; first-error halts
    runtime-double: Phase-5 AGENCY-VERIFY runtime double-checks pass-completeness

  § F5.5 — Σ-mask packed-bitmap (T11-D137)
    crate         : cssl-substrate-prime-directive::sigma
    type          : SigmaMaskPacked (16B std430)
    spec-anchor   : Omniverse/01_AXIOMS/04_AGENCY_INVARIANT § II
    contents      : consent_bits(32) + sovereignty_handle(16) +
                    capacity_floor(16) + reversibility_scope(16) +
                    audit_seq(16) + agency_state(16) + reserved(16)
    invariant     : audit_seq monotone-increasing per cell — mutation
                    that-doesn't-advance-seq = bug

  § PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (F5)
    F5 IS the structural encoding of PRIME-DIRECTIVE §1 anti-surveillance.
    biometric-family egress-ban is non-overridable. Σ-mask per-cell consent
    is the cell-level enforcement of Axiom-4 AGENCY-INVARIANT.

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ F6 : OBSERVABILITY  (path-hash + biometric-refusal + real BLAKE3+Ed25519)

  § THESIS
    F6 ≡ telemetry + audit-chain are first-class. raw-paths NEVER logged.
    biometric egress-refused at runtime ring-boundary as defense-in-depth.
    audit-chain signed via Ed25519 ; data-hashed via BLAKE3.

  § F6.1 — path-hash-only logging discipline (T11-D130)
    crate         : cssl-telemetry::path_hash
    spec-anchor   : specs/22_TELEMETRY.csl § PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ENFORCEMENT
                    + PRIME_DIRECTIVE.md §1 anti-surveillance
    type          : PathHasher (BLAKE3 + per-installation salt)
    type          : PathHash (newtype around [u8; 32])
    discipline    : raw paths NEVER stored in audit + ring + exporters
                    only-32-byte-BLAKE3 hash under per-installation salt
                    deterministic-within-process (correlation-allowed)
                    NON-portable across installations (anti-fingerprinting)
    Display       : 16-hex + ellipsis (short-form) so format!-ing never
                    produces a 64-char hex-blob mistaken for path

  § F6.2 — Biometric-compile-refusal at telemetry-ring (T11-D132)
    crate         : cssl-telemetry::biometric_refusal
    spec-anchor   : F5.2 above + PRIME_DIRECTIVE.md §1
    P18           : BiometricEgress process-abort runtime-defense
                    if biometric-family value reaches ring-boundary
    structural    : compile-time refusal via TelemetryEgress::for_domain
                    runtime is defense-in-depth (catches dynamic dispatch)

  § F6.3 — Real BLAKE3 + Ed25519 crypto integration (T11-D131)
    crate         : cssl-telemetry::audit (extends with real-crypto)
    blake3        : workspace dep blake3 = "1.x"
    ed25519       : workspace dep ed25519-dalek = "2.x"
    audit-chain   : every entry signed with Apocky-Root key-handle
                    signature appended to chain ; verifiable post-hoc
    R16-binding   : audit-chain root-hash embedded in OmegaAttestation
                    (build_id + compiler_id + runtime_id + substrate_id)
    R18-ring      : telemetry-ring lock-free producer-consumer ;
                    schema versioned ; scope-tagged

  § F6.4 — Telemetry surface modules
    crate         : cssl-telemetry
    modules       : audit ring schema scope exporter biometric_refusal path_hash
    discipline    : ring drains non-blocking ; bounded-ring fills+drops
                    when ConsentToken<telemetry-egress> revoked

  § PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ALIGNMENT (F6)
    Path-hash makes raw-paths surveillance-class data structurally
    inaccessible to logs. Biometric-refusal compile-time + runtime
    defense-in-depth. Real-crypto audit-chain prevents tampering.
    Together : §1 anti-surveillance + §4 transparency + §11 attestation
    encoded in the observability layer.

